news.title: Swiss Life posts net profit of 1.11 billion francs in 2023
news.para: Strong demand in the face of tight supply as well as stabilising rates meant there were "clear indications on the macrolevel" that property would recover over 2024, Matthias Aellig said on a call with investors on Thursday.

news.title: Germany's Vonovia posts net loss of 7.35 billion in 2023
news.para: Germany is undergoing a major change of fortune after an end to the era of cheap money that fed a decade-long property boom, hitting property companies like Vonovia hard.

news.title: UK's Berkeley underscores persistent tough sales conditions
news.para: The UK housing market has seen signs of stability at the start of 2024 on easing mortgage rates after battling subdued demand for most of last year.

news.title: China’s new home prices drop by 1.4% in February 2024
news.para: New home prices fell 0.3% month-on-month, in line with January's decline, according to Reuters calculations based on National Bureau of Statistics (NBS) data.

news.title: Four financial service firms purchase electoral bonds worth Rs 87 crore
news.para: As per the direction of the Supreme Court, the State Bank of India (SBI) on Tuesday evening submitted to the Election Commission the details of entities, which had purchased the now-scrapped electoral bonds and political parties which received them.

news.title: Odisha: NGT panel to examine excess sand mining issue in Brahmani river
news.para: The bench of B Amit Sthalekar (Judicial Member) and Arun Kumar Verma (Expert Member) said, “Considering the allegations made, we deem it appropriate to constitute a committee to elicit the veracity of the allegations.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh: Four housing development bodies pulled up for delaying affordable homes
news.para: The authorities governing Hapur-Pilkhuwa, Unnao-Shuklaganj, Kanpur and Ghaziabad have been asked to expedite work on creating the housing units which have been approved by the central sanctioning and monitoring committee (CSMC).

news.title: Mysuru development body set to auction 200 premium sites worth Rs 400 crore
news.para: Adish Sagar from Mysore Realtors’ Association said since the urban development body was unsuccessful in creating new layouts, it started selling off its premium sites in layouts it had developed earlier.

news.title: Brihanmumbai civic body issues list of top ten property tax defaulters
news.para: According to a BMC release on Thursday,property tax department officials pursued recovery of dues from defaulters across the 24 wards in the city.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body extends 5% rebate on paying property tax for 2024-25 till July
news.para: BBMP chief commissioner Tushar Giri Nath issued a circular on Wednesday stating that the Palike’s revenue officials would be busy with election duty and may not be available to create challans, provide information, or provide guidance to taxpayers.

news.title: DB Realty raises Rs 920 crore via qualified institutional placement
news.para: The board also approved incorporation of Advent International, a wholly-owned subsidiary, to acquire the DB Realty's interests in the hospitality business through an NCLT scheme of arrangement (demerger) process.

news.title: New ready reckoner rates in Maharashtra unlikely before Lok Sabha polls
news.para: A source in the govt on Wednesday said the state would consider the LS polls and the of the real estate market sentiment before deciding on the rates. “The elections are likely to affect the announcement of the RR rates.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government cancels land acquisition notification in Amaravati
news.para: The previous TDP govt had pooled up about 34,000 acres of land from farmers in 29 villages which were earmarked as capital city area through the land pooling scheme (LPS).

news.title: ICICI Prudential Life leases 2.52 lakh sq ft office space in Mumbai
news.para: The insurance major has leased this office space - spread across four floors - for five years through a structured deal, a person cited earlier said, adding that the company will be paying a monthly rental of 91.5 per sq ft for the office space.

news.title: Haryana: 20 illegal colonies razed, DTCP urges cops for FIRs
news.para: “These illegal colonies were developed in Gurgaon, Sohna, Pataudi and Farrukhnagar in the past few months,” an official said.

news.title: NCLT-appointed committee asks JAL to hand over nine projects in Jaypee Wish Town
news.para: The National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT)-appointed implementation and monitoring committee (IMC) wrote to JIL’s holding company Jaiprakash Associates Ltd (JAL) earlier this week, seeking possession of towers at these nine projects immediately.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh to establish town and country planning directorate
news.para: Under the plan, a town and country planning directorate will be set up, which will govern the development not only within the housing development authorities but also within urban local bodies.

news.title: Mumbai: No possession for three years, buyers protest against Bhagwati Developers
news.para: The Bhagwati Greens-III housing project next to ISKCON temple has three wings with 135 flats and 25 shops. Both A & B wings have 28 floors with 44 and 66 flats, respectively, while the C wing has 25 floors with 25 flats and 25 shops.

news.title: Delhi development body opens booking for 10,000 ready flats
news.para: Delhi Development Authority offers diverse flats in Narela under Diwali Special Housing Scheme 2023 Phase III. MIG flats in Sector A1-A4 are also available. Jasola, Rohini, Loknayak Puram feature varied affordable housing options.

news.title: US: Lennar Corp posts revenue of $7.33 billion in quarter ended February 2024
news.para: "Macroeconomic environment remained relatively consistent throughout the quarter," said Stuart Miller, Lennar's co-CEO, and added that housing supply remained chronically short due to production deficits over a decade.
